<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000024#     2#          234#">Va. Code Ann. § 24.2-234</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_24.2-234"/><heading><desig>§ 24.2-234.</desig><title>Removal of officer appointed for a term certain</title></heading><bodyText><p>Any officer appointed to an office for a term established by law may be removed from office, under the provisions of § 24.2-233, upon a petition filed with the circuit court in whose jurisdiction the officer resides signed by the person or a majority of the members of the authority who appointed him, if the appointing person or authority is not given the unqualified power of removal.</p><p>The circuit court also shall proceed pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 24.2-235"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 24.2-235">§ 24.2-235<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000024#     2#          235#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> for the removal of a member of a local electoral board or general registrar upon a petition signed by a majority of the members of the State Board of Elections as provided in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 24.2-103"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 24.2-103">§ 24.2-103<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000024#     2#          103#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText><hi